-- Normalize order items with product and category information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        p.category_id,
        oi.quantity,
        oi.unit_price
    FROM order_items oi
    LEFT JOIN products p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
)
SELECT * FROM source

-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to approved returns per item (one return record per item)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END ASC,
            return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_items_with_returns.sql
```sql
-- Join items to returns, flagging which items have approved returns
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.category_id,
        oi.quantity,
        CASE WHEN r.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- fct_return_rate_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        COUNT(ir.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(ir.is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
        ROUND(
            SUM(ir.is_returned)::DECIMAL / COUNT(ir.item_id),
            4
        ) AS return_rate
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} ir
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = ir.category_id
    GROUP BY
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY category_name ASC
